in translation but i stated i did not expect to pay full bill as felt hotel was poorly maintained.next morning at check -out met with surprise about my asking for bill to be reduced,manager said it could not be done as i could have changed rooms and refused to......clearly something lost in translation......being of sub-saharan descent choosing to sleep in igloo is not something i would have done by choice....that was lost on her.The heavily pregnant manager that was on duty either used her pregnancy as means of getting out of dealing with the issue or was just not fit to discharge her duties but started rubbing her tummy and wincing and ran to the toilet mid-conversation .....maybe thats another health and safety issue 987 should look into.paid in ful......will contact Expedia agents i booked through.987 has some work to do....Barcelona has many hotels that are centrally located and that put the health and safety of their customers first.sorry customer service from manager,poor leadership let the hotel down can see why they have let themselves down,others worked hard....but need to be managed by someone on the ball,aware of customers needs who lnows about healtha nd safety issues and is in a condition to discharge their duties.these are basics...Dont go to 987. 
