<Content>Stylish but Hot Hot Hot Date: 25th August 2008We went out to Barcelona and stayed for one week at the beautifully stylish 987 Barcelona. The welcome was Luke warm although I think it was just an end of a shift for this particular person as the staff were friendly and helpful once we had settled in. The room on first impressions was very stylish and had all the bits you needed to survive including the extortionately priced mini - bar! All seemed well until the first nights sleep and it dawned on me and my partner the foreign migrant with only one lung up in the roof space did not seem quite adequate air conditioning for the top floor sauna we were staying in... at least I lost some weight this week! This seemed to change into Siberia when you went down into the bar and dining room areas (I kid you not my girlfriend asked for a jumper when it was 35 degrees outside!). This aside these areas were very stylish and were actually quite nice to relax in after you had been out all day. The menu and food there seemed ok I only tried this once as we eat out elsewhere most of the time just abit of a limited choice but very nice and well presented. the location by far is the best asset of this hotel it was nearby to a metro which could get you to anywhere in Barcelona or if you wished most things were within walking distance tops walk was an hour walk to the zoo although we did find we went the long way round! (PS it's very easy to get lost here get a MAP!). If you or your partner are retails addicts and you want a bit of high class shopping then this is ideal for making you bankrupt as it is only a mere ten minute walk until you find you have no money for your holiday after one purchase at GUCCI, LOIUS VITTON or other names of such indulgence. I would recommend that you look up the restaurants before you go out to Barcelona there are some really nice ones but there is a lot of tosh that makes Mac Donald鈥檚 look like a gourmet restaurant! The good one's seem to be scattered about and not always on the main streets so don't be afraid to have a wonder as you might find some real gems like we did. One I do recommend is LA BO TIGA there are a few of these they are reasonably priced very stylish and the foods really good too which is a bonus!Overall I would recommend this hotel just try not to get a top floor room as these are really hot. 
