<Author>willybee
<Content>New  Enter this modern hotel by an anonymous doorway off Calla de Mallorca (10mins walk NE from Place de Catalunya)- no sign, nameplate or flags. It had only been open for 3 weeks when we stayed, so a sign may be on order!Very minimalist black ramp and 4 crushed velvet chairs lead you to reception. Friendly multi-lingual staff.Everything brand new - swift, whisper quiet elevators waft you to your floor. You can't miss your room - the room numbers are sculptures in themselves.Room comfortable. Huge firm bed, BUT - no wardrobes or drawers (just a tiny hanging space and open shelves). Nowhere to work, just a surface you can't sit at, let alone use a laptop.Green glass door with 10mm gaps all round lead to the bathroom without an extractor fan (or loo brush either for that matter).Shower is overhead - all or nothing but hot and powerful.We paid extra for breakfast - don't! Very ordinary - some hot dishes which had been prepared at 7am. then left in hot trays. The eggs were solid rubber. The orange juice from a packet. The coffee from a cheap push button machine (which broke).Overview - clean  new - enthusiastic friendly staff - would stay there again. 
